summary: I REALLY want to know how Crowley decided that he can call Aziraphale “angel”. Because he didn’t do it during their early...
body:
I REALLY want to know how Crowley decided that he can call Aziraphale “angel”. Because he didn’t do it during their early meetings, and this idea was clearly borrowed from people.

How was it? Did he hear someone calling their companion “angel” and was confused? because this “angel” was in fact human? And then he asked why did they say that and this person was like

— uhh. you’re being strange, dude. Because i feel like i am in heaven when we’re together.

— in heaven?

— yeah, like, i feel safe and comfort and great wish to be better. I feel like i’m in the right place to be. And that my life becomes brighter.

— not my heaven, but got the point

— my partner brings light into my life, so, “angel”

And then Crowley decided that it’s LITERALLY his case and began to call Aziraphale this way.
